cves.description: Grand Theft Auto V for PC allows attackers to achieve partial remote code execution or modify files on a PC, as exploited in the wild in January 2023. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice

Booked Scheduler 2.5.5 allows authenticated users to create and schedule events for any other user via a modified userId value to reservation_save.php. NOTE: 2.5.5 is a version from 2014. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice

In pkgconf through 1.9.3, variable duplication can cause unbounded string expansion due to incorrect checks in libpkgconf/tuple.c:pkgconf_tuple_parse. For example, a .pc file containing a few hundred bytes can expand to one billion bytes. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice

** DISPUTED ** KeePass through 2.53 (in a default installation) allows an attacker, who has write access to the XML configuration file, to obtain the cleartext passwords by adding an export trigger. NOTE: the vendor's position is that the password database is not intended to be secure against an attacker who has that l CVE project by @Sn0wAlice
A Host Header Injection issue on the Login page of Plesk Obsidian through 18.0.49 allows attackers to redirect users to malicious websites via a Host request header. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice

A Segmentation fault was found in UPX in PackLinuxElf64::invert_pt_dynamic() in p_lx_elf.cpp. An attacker with a crafted input file allows invalid memory address access that could lead to a denial of service. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice

A heap-based buffer overflow issue was discovered in UPX in PackTmt::pack() in p_tmt.cpp file. The flow allows an attacker to cause a denial of service (abort) via a crafted file. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice
Excessive Attack Surface in GitHub repository pyload/pyload prior to 0.5.0b3.dev41. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice
Improper Input Validation in GitHub repository pyload/pyload prior to 0.5.0b3.dev40. CVE project by @Sn0wAlice
